This is a template for [[WP:PetScan|PetScan]] (formerly CatScan)

PetScan searches categories recursively. It will find subcategories that overlap with other categories, templates, etc.

==Usage==
<pre>
{{PetScan
 | cat       =
 | catdepth  = (optional, defaults to 1)
 | cat2      = (optional)
 | cat2depth = (optional, defaults to catdepth/1)
 | templates = (optional)
 | linktext  =
 | note      = (optional, when used limits width to 250px for text wrapping)
 | type      = (optional. See below)
}}
</pre>

===Type options===
*'''plain''' -  makes the template into a plain text link instead of the boxed version.
*'''open''' - doesn't close the wikitable, allowing one to add other {{tl|catscan}} links (using <code>Type=plain</code>) in the same box. When used one must manually close the wikitable with <code>|}</code>

==Example usage==
The template places a box on the right-hand side of the page, which when clicked upon opens up a page to search on the parameters supplied.

;One category, one template
:''Featured articles'' containing the template ''{{tl|citation needed}}'')
:{{tlc|PetScan|2=cat=Featured articles|3=templates=citation needed|4=linktext=Featured articles needing citations}}{{PetScan|cat=Featured articles|templates=citation needed|linktext=Featured articles needing citations}}
;Two categories
:''Featured articles'' that are about ''English-language albums''
:{{tlc|PetScan|2=cat=Featured articles|3=cat2 = English-language albums|4=linktext=Featured articles about English-language albums}}{{PetScan|cat=Featured articles|cat2 = English-language albums|linktext=Featured articles about English-language albums}}

